[[tab About This Theme]]
[[include component:image-block name=https://scp-wiki.wdfiles.com/local--files/theme%3Arevised-ijamea-theme/IJAMEA2.png|caption=Image Sample|width=10px]]

[[[component:ijamea-theme|The IJAMEA theme]]] was created by [[*user Dr Solo]] but it was deleted. In 2020, [[[theme:revised-ijamea-theme|A new theme]]] was created by [[*user Nanigashi Sato]].

But the revised IJAMEA theme is one of [[[sigma-9-themes|Sigma-9 themes]]] which based on [[[component:theme|the Site theme]]]. In this site, there are another mainstream of themes. It is [[[black-highlighter-themes|BHL themes]]], which is based on [[[theme:black-highlighter-theme|Black Highlighter Theme]]].

This Theme is created for meeting the demand for a BHL theme, based on the revised IJAMEA theme.

"局査調例事常異國帝本日大" is traditional notation of "大日本帝國異常事例調査局", the Japanese notation for "Imperial Japanese Anomalous Matters Examination Agency". It's written from right to left and by a traditional form of kanji used in Japan before WW II.

And this logo was created by [[*user Nanimono Demonai]], I borrowed it from [*https://scp-jp.wikidot.com/foundation-or-goi-logo his artwork in JP]. Of course, it can be used under CC BY-SA 3.0. This logo is modeled on the letter "異" in [*https://en.m.wikipedia.org/wiki/Seal_script ancient seal script] and a butterfly(蝶/chō), which is pronounced the same as "調" in Japanese. "異調" stands for "**異**常事例**調**査局(AMEA, Anomalous Matters Examination Agency)".
[[/tab]]
[[tab Special Thanks]]
* [[*user Dr Solo]] (Developer of [[[component:ijamea-theme|Original Theme]]])
* [[*user Nanigashi Sato]] (Developer of [[[theme:revised-ijamea-theme|Revised IJAMEA Theme]]] and Special Adviser)
*  [[*user Maxyfran73]] (Special Adviser)
* [[*user aismallard]] (Special Adviser)
* [[*user stormbreath]] (Special Adviser)
* [[*user Nanimono Demonai]] (Creator of the new Logo of IJAMEA)
* And all contributors of [*/system:page-tags/tag/ijamea#pages the glory of IJAMEA and their country].
[[/tab]]
[[/tabview]]
